			<h2 class="title" id="post-890"><a href="http://cgvw.ics.uci.edu/san-francisco-moma-video-games-as-art-and-interaction-design/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to San Francisco MOMA: Video Games as Art and Interaction Design">San Francisco MOMA: Video Games as Art and Interaction Design</a></h2>
			<p class="meta"><span class="author">Posted by <a href="">staff</a>&nbsp;November 29th, 2012</span></p>
			<div class="entry">
			<p>The San Francisco Museum of Modern Art has acquired a collection of 14 video games of significant historical importance. This move is a recognition of video games as both Art and Interaction Design, and establishes the need to preserve these historical artifacts. Read MOMA&#8217;s full article for insightful remarks about its initiative.</p>
			</div>
						<p class="links">
				Posted in <a href="http://cgvw.ics.uci.edu/category/in-the-news/" title="View all posts in In the News" rel="category tag">In the News</a>				&nbsp;&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;
